<title>SWITZERLAND: FORECAST - Swiss GDP seen up 0.44 pct in 1997.</title>
<headline>FORECAST - Swiss GDP seen up 0.44 pct in 1997.</headline>
<dateline>ZURICH 1997-03-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Swiss Business Economists' Consensus (BEC) said it had revised its consensus forecast for Swiss 1997 gross domestic product growth to 0.44 percent from the 0.61 percent seen in December.</p>
<p>It gave these forecasts based on responses from 33 economists at banks, insurers, industrial companies, think tanks, and other groups (December data in brackets):</p>
<p>				1996	  1997	     1998</p>
<p> Real GDP growth (pct)  -0.7    +0.44 (0.61)   +1.68 (1.66)</p>
<p> Plant/equip investment +1.3    +0.90 (1.45)   +2.62 (3.08)</p>
<p> Real total exports     +2.4    +3.33 (3.25)   +4.50 (4.47)</p>
<p> Inflation		  +0.8    +1.00 (1.01)   +1.60 (1.54)</p>
<p> Unemployment rate	 4.7     5.43 (5.00)    5.28 (4.74)</p>
<p>Financial markets forecasts:</p>
<p>				20 March 97   End-June 97   End-March 98</p>
<p> Three-month Eurofrancs    1.88	    1.84	     2.38</p>
<p> Avg govt bond yield	 3.59	    3.55	     3.94</p>
<p> Mark/Swiss franc	   86.18	   86.65	    85.78</p>
<p> Dollar/Swiss franc	  1.44	    1.46	     1.43</p>
<p> Swiss Performance Index  2,829	   2,900	    2,998</p>
<p>-- Zurich newsroom +41 1 631 7340</p>
